 -- Function: poly_ideal_intersection (POLYLIST1, POLYLIST2, VARLIST)
     ‘poly_ideal_intersection’ returns the intersection of two ideals.


File: maxima-core-docs.info,  Node: Function poly_ideal_polysaturation polylist polylistlist varlist,  Next: Function poly_ideal_polysaturation1 polylist1 polylist2 varlist,  Prev: Function poly_ideal_intersection polylist1 polylist2 varlist,  Up: grobner

 -- Function: poly_ideal_polysaturation (POLYLIST, POLYLISTLIST,
          VARLIST)
     _polylistlist_ is a list of n list of polynomials
     ‘[polylist1,...,polylistn]’.  Returns the reduced Groebner basis of
     the saturation of the ideal

     I(polylist):I(polylist_1)^{inf:...:I(polylist_n)}inf


File: maxima-core-docs.info,  Node: Function poly_ideal_polysaturation1 polylist1 polylist2 varlist,  Next: Function poly_ideal_saturation polylist1 polylist2 varlist,  Prev: Function poly_ideal_polysaturation polylist polylistlist varlist,  Up: grobner

 -- Function: poly_ideal_polysaturation1 (POLYLIST1, POLYLIST2, VARLIST)
     _polylist2_ is a list of n polynomials ‘[poly1,...,polyn]’.
     Returns the reduced Groebner basis of the ideal

     I(polylist):poly1^{inf:...:polyn}inf

     obtained by a sequence of successive saturations in the polynomials
     of the polynomial list _polylist2_ of the ideal generated by the
     polynomial list _polylist1_.


File: maxima-core-docs.info,  Node: Function poly_ideal_saturation polylist1 polylist2 varlist,  Next: Function poly_ideal_saturation1 polylist poly varlist,  Prev: Function poly_ideal_polysaturation1 polylist1 polylist2 varlist,  Up: grobner

 -- Function: poly_ideal_saturation (POLYLIST1, POLYLIST2, VARLIST)
     Returns the reduced Groebner basis of the saturation of the ideal

     I(polylist1):I(polylist2)^inf

     Geometrically, over an algebraically closed field, this is the set
     of polynomials in the ideal generated by _polylist1_ which do not
     identically vanish on the variety of _polylist2_.


File: maxima-core-docs.info,  Node: Function poly_ideal_saturation1 polylist poly varlist,  Next: Function poly_lcm poly1 poly2 varlist,  Prev: Function poly_ideal_saturation polylist1 polylist2 varlist,  Up: grobner

 -- Function: poly_ideal_saturation1 (POLYLIST, POLY, VARLIST)
     Returns the reduced Groebner basis of the saturation of the ideal

     I(polylist):poly^inf

     Geometrically, over an algebraically closed field, this is the set
     of polynomials in the ideal generated by _polylist_ which do not
     identically vanish on the variety of _poly_.


File: maxima-core-docs.info,  Node: Function poly_lcm poly1 poly2 varlist,  Next: Function poly_minimization polylist varlist,  Prev: Function poly_ideal_saturation1 polylist poly varlist,  Up: grobner

 -- Function: poly_lcm (POLY1, POLY2, VARLIST)
     Returns the lowest common multiple of _poly1_ and _poly2_.


File: maxima-core-docs.info,  Node: Function poly_minimization polylist varlist,  Next: Variable poly_monomial_order,  Prev: Function poly_lcm poly1 poly2 varlist,  Up: grobner

 -- Function: poly_minimization (POLYLIST, VARLIST)
     Returns a sublist of the polynomial list _polylist_ spanning the
     same monomial ideal as _polylist_ but minimal, i.e. no leading
     monomial of a polynomial in the sublist divides the leading
     monomial of another polynomial.


File: maxima-core-docs.info,  Node: Variable poly_monomial_order,  Next: Function poly_multiply poly1 poly2 varlist,  Prev: Function poly_minimization polylist varlist,  Up: grobner

 -- Variable: poly_monomial_order
     Default value: ‘lex’

     This global switch controls which monomial order is used in
     polynomial and Groebner Bases calculations.  If not set, ‘lex’ will
     be used.


