 -- Function: poly_normal_form (POLY, POLYLIST, VARLIST)
     ‘poly_normal_form’ finds the normal form of a polynomial _poly_
     with respect to a set of polynomials _polylist_.


File: maxima-core-docs.info,  Node: Function poly_normalize poly varlist,  Next: Function poly_normalize_list polylist varlist,  Prev: Function poly_normal_form poly polylist varlist,  Up: grobner

 -- Function: poly_normalize (POLY, VARLIST)
     Returns the polynomial _poly_ divided by the leading coefficient.
     It assumes that the division is possible, which may not always be
     the case in rings which are not fields.


File: maxima-core-docs.info,  Node: Function poly_normalize_list polylist varlist,  Next: Function poly_polysaturation_extension poly polylist varlist1 varlist2,  Prev: Function poly_normalize poly varlist,  Up: grobner

 -- Function: poly_normalize_list (POLYLIST, VARLIST)
     ‘poly_normalize_list’ applies ‘poly_normalize’ to each polynomial
     in the list.  That means it divides every polynomial in a list
     _polylist_ by its leading coefficient.


