 -- Function: poly_polysaturation_extension (POLY, POLYLIST, VARLIST1,
          VARLIST2)


File: maxima-core-docs.info,  Node: Variable poly_primary_elimination_order,  Next: Function poly_primitive_part poly1 varlist,  Prev: Function poly_polysaturation_extension poly polylist varlist1 varlist2,  Up: grobner

 -- Variable: poly_primary_elimination_order
     Default value: ‘false’

     Name of the default order for eliminated variables in
     elimination-based functions.  If not set, ‘lex’ will be used.


File: maxima-core-docs.info,  Node: Function poly_primitive_part poly1 varlist,  Next: Function poly_pseudo_divide poly polylist varlist,  Prev: Variable poly_primary_elimination_order,  Up: grobner

 -- Function: poly_primitive_part (POLY1, VARLIST)
     Returns the polynomial _poly_ divided by the GCD of its
     coefficients.

     (%i1) poly_primitive_part(35*y+21*x,[x,y]);
     (%o1)                              5 y + 3 x


File: maxima-core-docs.info,  Node: Function poly_pseudo_divide poly polylist varlist,  Next: Function poly_reduced_grobner polylist varlist,  Prev: Function poly_primitive_part poly1 varlist,  Up: grobner

 -- Function: poly_pseudo_divide (POLY, POLYLIST, VARLIST)
     Pseudo-divide a polynomial _poly_ by the list of n polynomials
     _polylist_.  Return multiple values.  The first value is a list of
     quotients a.  The second value is the remainder r.  The third
     argument is a scalar coefficient c, such that c*poly can be divided
     by _polylist_ within the ring of coefficients, which is not
     necessarily a field.  Finally, the fourth value is an integer count
     of the number of reductions performed.  The resulting objects
     satisfy the equation:

     c*poly=sum(a[i]*polylist[i],i=1...n)+r.


File: maxima-core-docs.info,  Node: Function poly_reduced_grobner polylist varlist,  Next: Function poly_reduction polylist varlist,  Prev: Function poly_pseudo_divide poly polylist varlist,  Up: grobner

 -- Function: poly_reduced_grobner (POLYLIST, VARLIST)
     Returns a reduced Groebner basis of the ideal span by the
     polynomials _polylist_.  Affected by the global flags.


File: maxima-core-docs.info,  Node: Function poly_reduction polylist varlist,  Next: Variable poly_return_term_list,  Prev: Function poly_reduced_grobner polylist varlist,  Up: grobner

 -- Function: poly_reduction (POLYLIST, VARLIST)
     ‘poly_reduction’ reduces a list of polynomials _polylist_, so that
     each polynomial is fully reduced with respect to the other
     polynomials.


File: maxima-core-docs.info,  Node: Variable poly_return_term_list,  Next: Function poly_s_polynomial poly1 poly2 varlist,  Prev: Function poly_reduction polylist varlist,  Up: grobner

 -- Variable: poly_return_term_list
     Default value: ‘false’

     If set to ‘true’, all functions in this package will return each
     polynomial as a list of terms in the current monomial order rather
     than a _maxima_ general expression.


File: maxima-core-docs.info,  Node: Function poly_s_polynomial poly1 poly2 varlist,  Next: Function poly_saturation_extension poly polylist varlist1 varlist2,  Prev: Variable poly_return_term_list,  Up: grobner

 -- Function: poly_s_polynomial (POLY1, POLY2, VARLIST)
     Returns the _syzygy polynomial_ (_S-polynomial_) of two polynomials
     _poly1_ and _poly2_.


