 -- Variable: poly_secondary_elimination_order
     Default value: ‘false’

     Name of the default order for kept variables in elimination-based
     functions.  If not set, ‘lex’ will be used.


File: maxima-core-docs.info,  Node: Function poly_subtract poly1 poly2 varlist,  Next: Variable poly_top_reduction_only,  Prev: Variable poly_secondary_elimination_order,  Up: grobner

 -- Function: poly_subtract (POLY1, POLY2, VARLIST)
     Subtracts a polynomial _poly2_ from _poly1_.

     (%i1) poly_subtract(z+x^2*y,x-z,[x,y,z]);
                                           2
     (%o1)                          2 z + x  y - x


File: maxima-core-docs.info,  Node: Variable poly_top_reduction_only,  Prev: Function poly_subtract poly1 poly2 varlist,  Up: grobner

 -- Variable: poly_top_reduction_only
     Default value: ‘false’

     If not ‘false’, use top reduction only whenever possible.  Top
     reduction means that division algorithm stops after the first
     reduction.


